The Cinderteeth: Seismic Risk Assessment

Hazard Registry, Bureau of Route Stability
Filed under: Geological Threat, Conclave Liability, Trade Disruption

The Cinderteeth Mountains are not Midgaard's territory. They are
Midgaard's problem. Every tremor in that volcanic arc translates
into route instability, convoy losses, and emergency requisitions
drawn against the city's grain reserves.

The Ash Winters proved this. Eruptions sent ash clouds across the
continent, contaminating wells, poisoning the Great Northern Forest's
streams, devastating Kowloon's delta. Our ledgers from those years
are stained with emergency ink -- red-bordered entries marking crisis
expenditures that nearly bankrupted the Passage Tithe. The Bureau of
Route Stability was founded in the aftermath.

The Hazard Doctrine maintained by the range's route houses is, to
our assessment, entirely sensible. The Silent Bell Protocol mirrors
our own emergency lamp procedures. The Double-water doctrine is the
kind of hard-won operational law our Oath of the Kept Record was
designed to preserve. We recognize institutional rigor even where our
jurisdiction does not reach.

What we cannot forgive is the Spirebound Conclave.

Our ledgers contain the evidence. Archive drawer seven, requisition
volume nineteen: entries recording payment for condemned debtors
transferred to the mountain academy. "Forty iron bars and six
condemned debtors" -- our citizens, sent to isolation that made
research possible and accountability impossible. We enabled the
Conclave with bodies and iron. When it collapsed, leaving unretrieved
resonance crystals at fault intersections, we bore partial
responsibility for every sympathetic tremor since.

The Ash Cult that claims eruptions pronounce divine verdict against
civic corruption is, our Bureau notes with discomfort, not entirely
wrong about the corruption -- only about the divinity.

Six subregions in our threat assessments: the Ember Crown rated
impassable, the Bellspine rated severe-disorientation, the
Chalkwind Saddles rated viable-with-escort, the Glasswash Fans
rated extractable, the Blackstep Footholds where our jurisdiction
technically begins, and the Western Fold formally designated:
do not approach without tribunal authorization.

The mountains remind us that seismic risk is also moral risk. What
the city sent into those peaks has not finished returning.
